parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive RTV Silicone in Engine Oil System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive RTV silicone in the engine oil system can cause oil starvation, leading to engine failure, which can result in accidents, fires, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: excessive RTV silicone in the oil pan filler tube
residue of silicone in the engine dipstick
clogged oil mesh net and pump

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Starvation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure due to oil starvation can cause accidents, fires, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: excessive RTV silicone in the oil pan filler tube
residue of silicone in the engine dipstick
clogged oil mesh net and pump

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Warranty Coverage and Diagnostic Information
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of warranty coverage and diagnostic information can leave vehicle owners with significant repair costs and uncertainty about the cause of the engine failure.
symptoms: and unclear cause of engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Turn Signal Failure due to Direct Sunlight
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear turn signals to function properly when the vehicle is exposed to direct sunlight can lead to accidents or citations, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The rear turn signals do not illuminate
hyperflash on the dash and front of the vehicle
and only function normally when a shadow is cast upon the affected turn signal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Circuit Failure due to Sun Exposure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical circuit can cause the dome light to fail, which can lead to reduced visibility and safety issues, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The dome light on the driver's side fails to function
and the circuit area seems to die when the car sits in the sun.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive RTV (Room Temperature Vulcanizing) Sealant in Oil Pan
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive RTV sealant in the oil pan can break off and block the engine oil tube filter, causing the engine to run dry and leading to engine failure.
symptoms: RTV sealant visible in the oil pan
RTV sealant blocking the engine oil tube filter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal can cause confusion or accidents on the road, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
